Fall Shelf Styling REVEAL...⁣
⁣
If you saw my stories the past couple of days then you know I have been switching up my dining room shelves for fall!  I hope you are ready, because I took you along on the entire messy process!  Good thing I will only have to make small adjustments over the next few months to alter the decor for the different seasons and holidays!!⁣
⁣
Also, as I mentioned, I’ve teamed up with 4 talented friends to bring you some great shelf styling inspiration! ⁣
⁣
Please head over to all of these accounts to see how they style shelves. You will be inspired!⁣

I know that I have mentioned before that I often times struggle with styling shelves.  It’s hard for me to find a balance between too many items, not enough items, and the right selection of pieces. I am finally happy with the way my dining room shelves have turned out, and I wanted to share with you some of the strategies that I used to create a simple, balanced and carefully curated look. 
I now have a link in my bio for you to easily access my @LIKEtoKNOW.it, Amazon Store, and my Pinterest page!  Now you can quickly and easily shop my home.

You asked for it…⁣
⁣
⁣
I have yet to decorate my front porch for Fall this year, but so many of you requested Front Porch Fall Inspo that I decided to post a throwback to LAST YEARS Fall Front Porch.⁣
⁣
Up until I pull out Halloween Decor I stick with seasonal flowers, woven rugs, baskets, a fun doormat, and wreaths.  Adding texture and deeper toned flowers instantly makes me want to sip a mug of apple cider!  The kids want to make an Apple Pie tonight and that always gives me major Fall vibes and I can’t say that I’m mad about it. 😉⁣
⁣
This years front porch is coming soon! Everything here is out of stock but if you want to Shop my Home head to the link in my Bio!⁣ Head to Stories later for some Front Porch Links!

node.text:
Do you ever move your furniture around for a fresh look?⁣
⁣
⁣
Last Fall I arranged my furniture in this layout and loved the openness from the front door.  After Christmas I moved it back to the usual set up, but decided it was time to swap it back.  Such a great way to give your home a fresh new look without purchasing a single new item! ⁣
⁣
So many touches of Fall are giving my home cozier vibe to go with the cooler temps and rain we had had over the last couple of weeks.  I love this time of year, and all of the fun that follows over the next 4 months!  Later today head on over to Stories for some tips and curated collections on how to transition your home into the cooler and cozier months! ⁣

node.text:
Is there a missed opportunity in your home?⁣
⁣
For the first year that we lived in our home this little hallway outside of our Primary Bedroom sat blank. No cabinet, no art, no chair or basket…just completely bare!  I felt like it wasn’t functional as far as sitting or hanging out went, so why decorate it?  One day I had a vision and this is what transpired.  What once was a boring white hallway is now a space that puts a smile on my face every single day!  I love the incredible pictures of my family, and the cabinet is by far one of my favorite pieces of furniture in my home!⁣
⁣
Do you have any blank spaces in your home that you could add a little pizzazz to?  I promise you that you will love it!⁣

What is the biggest NO REGRETS decision you had to make in your home?⁣
⁣
⁣
In order to have our Dining Room Bar Area I had to give up a Walk In Pantry.  While I drool over the stunning steel doors that head into Butler Pantry Areas, I have never one time regretted the decision to set up our Kitchen and Dining space this way. They are very much connected, yet feel like very independent spaces with their own identity.  It’s amazing what paint can do…it defines an area and allows the space to stand out.⁣
⁣
I would love to hear what decisions you had to make and if you have regrets!  Hopefully you are as happy as I am!⁣

Looking to add warmth and detail to a space?⁣
⁣
⁣
In 2 hours, and an investment of less than $50, this beautiful beam that I found at a lumber yard dramatically changed the look and feel of our entire kitchen. I lightly sanded the raw natural unstained beam, predrilled holes for the 6” deck screws, removed the drywall, and mounted to the studs in the wall. We also had some minor drywall repair around the beam as well. ⁣
⁣
For a small investment of time and money our Kitchen now has a more custom feel.  I love the added natural element and detail that the raw wood adds to the space. This is something you could also do for a fireplace mantle or even doorway to add custom details to your home!⁣
⁣

TOP 5 AMAZON in my home : Part One⁣
⁣
⁣
I have so many Amazon pieces in my home that it was hard to choose so I decided to start with my most asked about and Best Sellers from this year!⁣
⁣
48” Chandelier:  My linear Dining Room light is actually from RH, but I prefer the muted gold tone of this Dupe over the real deal.  At 1/4 of the price of other retailers this statement light is a must buy!⁣
⁣
8’ Mantel Beam:  We had custom brackets made to attach this raw wood beam over our fireplace. It added just the right natural element to our Great Room. ⁣
⁣
Faux Boxwoods:  I am generally a real plant kind of girl, but these faux shrubs just might be my favorite purchase of 2021!  No watering, no wet front porch, no dead leaves…they are pretty much perfect!  They will also be beautiful with holiday lights on!  Last week in Seattle large boxwoods similar to these lined the front of the 5 story RH Store. ⁣
⁣
Faux Linen Panels:  These curtain panels were my Top Seller in 2020 and 2021!  I have two versions in my home that are not only beautiful, but more affordable!⁣
⁣
Wood Saddle Stool:  I really wanted a cute wood stool for our new bathroom, but I didn’t want to spend $150+. For $40 I decided to give this beauty a try and had planned on beating it up a bit, but it was perfect just as it is!⁣
⁣
⁣

“Do you use all new pieces each time you style your shelves?”⁣
⁣
⁣
This is one of the questions that I was asked after my Shelf Styling series last week, and the answer is no. I have three sets of open shelving in my home…The Dining Room, Laundry Room, and in our Primary Bedroom. I also have two cabinets with glass doors that I style. The only area that I typically restyle completely each season is my Dining Room shelves. They are such a focal point in our home that I enjoy changing them up almost entirely,  otherwise I only swap out a couple different pieces in the other areas. ⁣
⁣
I just recently changed up My Primary Bedroom shelves and decided to add in a black vase and bowl for a moody vibe, and swapped in a new Target bowl and seasonal faux stems. Just a few minor changes completely changed the look and feel of this entire space. Once I create a balance that I love I don’t like to mess it up too much. 😉 ⁣
⁣
